3:
When people die, you cause their corpses to become soil again;
\q2 you change their corpses to become dirt like that from which the first man was created.
\q1

7:
Similarly, because of the sins that we commit, you become angry with us;
\q2 you terrify us and then you destroy us.
\q1

8:
It is as though you place our sins in front of you;
\q2 you spread out even our secret sins where you can see them.
\q1

9:
Because you are angry with us, you cause our lives to end;
\q2 the years that we live pass as quickly as a sigh does.
\q1

10:
People live for only seventy years;
\q2 if they are strong, some of them live for eighty years.
\q1 But even during good years we have much pain and troubles;
\q2 our lives soon end, and we die.
\b
\q1

17:
Lord, our God, give us your blessings
\q2 and enable us to be successful;
\q2 yes, cause us to be successful in everything that we do!
